details:
Case 66 is a 28 year-old male Singapore Citizen with no recent travel history to China. He is linked to the cluster at Grace Assembly of God.

He reported onset of symptoms on 29 January and had sought treatment at a GP clinic on 2 February, 5 February and 12 February. He was referred to NCID on 12 February. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 14 February morning.

Prior to hospital admission, he had gone to work at Grace Assembly of God, and attended church services at Godâ€™s Kingdom Bread of Life Church (37 Jalan Permimpin). He stays at Mei Hwan Drive.
